		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-size:10pt;">There are no per meeting fees for standing committee meetings.&nbsp;&nbsp;Loan Committee members are paid $500 for each Management Loan Committee meeting attended and Ad-Hoc Committee members are paid $500 for each meeting attended.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-size:10pt;">The Chairman does not receive per meeting fees or committee retainers.&nbsp;&nbsp;The CEO does not receive retainers or per meeting fees for Board or Board committee service. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">Stock-based Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The Corporation&#x2019;s 2014 Equity Incentive Plan (&#x201C;2014 Plan&#x201D;) allows for the granting of equity awards to non-employee directors of the Corporation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Equity compensation for directors consists of restricted stock units (&#x201C;RSUs&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;The number of RSUs granted to the Chairman and each non-employee director is in accordance with a methodology approved by the Compensation Commit</font><font style="display: inline;">tee and ratified by the Board.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">RSUs granted prior to 2016 are generally convertible into shares of Common Stock after three years provided certain performance criteria are met (&#x201C;performance-based RSUs&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;RSUs granted to non-employee directors in 2016, 2017 and 2018 are time-based RSUs that vest ratably and convert into shares of Common Stock over a three-year time period.&nbsp;&nbsp;The RSUs granted in January 2016 also receive annual cash dividend equivalents at the same rate as the dividends declared by the Board on the Corporation&#x2019;s Common Stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;The ability to convert performance-based RSUs into shares of Common Stock after three years and the related conversion ratio is determined in the same manner as for executive officers described in the &#x201C;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#x201D; in this proxy statement.&nbsp;&nbsp;All outstanding RSUs granted to directors immediately vest upon an involuntary termination following a change in control, total and permanent disability or death.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;"></font><font style="display: inline;">10</font><font style="display: inline;"></font>

		</p>

			<a href="#TableofContents"><font style="display: inline;font-size:8pt;">Table of Contents</font></a>

		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">Retirement Plan</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">On June 18, 1991, the Board of the Bank adopted The First National Bank of Long Island Retirement Plan for Directors ("Retirement Plan").&nbsp;&nbsp;Effective December 31, 2000, benefits earned to date under the Retirement Plan were frozen and the ability of directors to earn additional benefits was discontinued.&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon retirement after attaining the age of sixty (60), each of the current directors who was a director prior to 2001 will receive a credit ("Credit Percentage") of ten percent (10%) multiplied by the number of years of service on the Board through December 31, 2000, not to exceed one hundred percent (100%).&nbsp;&nbsp;The annual benefit ("Annual Benefit") payable under the Retirement Plan is equal to the monthly Board of Directors&#x2019; attendance fee in effect as of December 31, 2000, which was $1,000, multiplied by twelve (12) and then multiplied by the Credit Percentage.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Annual Benefit is payable in quarterly installments for a period of seven (7) years from the date of retirement ("Payment Period").&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event of the death of a director or a retired director, the surviving spouse of such director is entitled to receive an annual payment equal to seventy-five percent (75%) of the Annual Benefit, calculated as set forth above, and payable over the remainder of the applicable Payment Period.&nbsp;&nbsp;Messrs. Canarick, Hogan and Teagle are the only directors participating in the Retirement Plan.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Mr. Hilton joined the Bank in June 2017 as Senior Vice President and Commercial Banking Division Executive.&nbsp;&nbsp;On January 1, 2018, Mr. Hilton was promoted to Executive Vice President of the Corporation and the Bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;Prior to joining the Bank, Mr. Hilton served as Executive Vice President &amp; Chief Credit Officer of Suffolk County National Bank and its holding company, Suffolk Bancorp, until its acquisition by People&#x2019;s United Bank in April 2017.&nbsp; Mr. Hilton joined People&#x2019;s United Bank and served as Senior Credit Officer until May 2017.&nbsp; Prior to his employment at Suffolk County National Bank, Mr. Hilton served as Executive Vice President &amp; Chief Credit Officer of Empire National Bank and Vice President of its h</font><font style="display: inline;">olding company, Empire Bancorp.</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">PROP</font><a name="Proposal2"></a><font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">OSAL 2</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">NON-BINDING, ADVISORY VOTE TO APPROVE THE COMPENSATION PAID TO THE</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">CORPORATION&#x2019;S NAMED EXECUTIVE OFFICERS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The compensation paid to our NEOs is disclosed in this proxy statement in the sections entitled &#x201C;Compensation Discussion and Analysis,&#x201D; &#x201C;Compensation of Executive Officers,&#x201D; &#x201C;Compensation Pursuant to Plans&#x201D; and &#x201C;Employment Agreements.&#x201D;&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that our compensation policies, practices and decisions are focused on pay-for-performance principles and are strongly aligned with the long-term best interests of our stockholders.&nbsp;&nbsp;Compensation of our NEOs is designed to enable us to attract and retain talented and experienced senior executives to lead the Corporation successfully in a competitive environment.&nbsp;&nbsp;Stockholders are being asked to cast a non-binding, advisory vote on the following resolution:</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">RESOLVED, that the compensation paid to the Corporation&#x2019;s NEOs as disclosed in its proxy statement for the April 17, 2018 Annual Meeting of Stockholders pursuant to Item 402 of Regulation S-K, including the Compensation Discussion and Analysis, compensation tables and narrative discussion, is hereby APPROVED. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The affirmative vote of the holders of a majority of shares represented in person or by proxy and voting on this item will be required for approval.</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Your vote on this Proposal 2 is advisory, and therefore not binding on the Corporation, the Compensation Committee or the Board.&nbsp;&nbsp;The vote will not be construed to overrule any decision by the Corporation, the Compensation Committee or the Board; to create or imply any change to the fiduciary duties of the Corporation, the Compensation Committee or the Board; or to create or imply any additional fiduciary duties for the Corporation, the Compensation Committee or the Board.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, our Board and our Compensation Committee value the opinions of our stockholders and to the extent there is a significant vote against the compensation paid to our NEOs as disclosed in this proxy statement, we will consider our stockholders&#x2019; concerns and the Board and the Compensation Committee will evaluate whether any actions are necessary to address those concerns.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">The Board of Directors recommends a vote FOR the proposal to approve the</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">compensation paid to the Corporation&#x2019;s named executive officers.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;"></font><font style="display: inline;">12</font><font style="display: inline;"></font>

		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">APPROVAL OF AN AMENDMENT TO THE CERTIFICATE OF INCORPORATION TO INCREASE </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">THE NUMBER OF AUTHORIZED SHARES OF COMMON STOCK</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The Board recommends approval of an amendment of Article Fifth of the Corporation&#x2019;s Certificate of Incorporation to increase the number of authorized shares of Common Stock from forty million (40,000,000) shares to eighty million (80,000,000) shares.&nbsp;&nbsp;If approved by the stockholders, </font><font style="display: inline;">Article </font><font style="display: inline;">Fifth</font><font style="display: inline;"> of </font><font style="display: inline;">the Corporation</font><font style="display: inline;">&#x2019;s Certificate of Incorporation would b</font><font style="display: inline;">e amended by deleting the first sentence thereof </font><font style="display: inline;">in its entirety, and substituting in lieu thereof the following: </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">&#x201C;The aggregate number of shares which this Corporation shall have authority to issue is 80,000,000 shares, par value $0.10 each, which shall be known as &#x2018;Common Stock&#x2019;.&#x201D;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The remainder of Article Fifth shall remain unchanged by the proposed amendment.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The Board believes that the proposed increase in the authorized shares of Common Stock is in the best interest of the Corporation and its stockholders.&nbsp;&nbsp;As of March 1, 2018, the Corporation had 25,018,449 shares of Common Stock issued and outstanding, 2,2</font><font style="display: inline;">92</font><font style="display: inline;">,</font><font style="display: inline;">938</font><font style="display: inline;"> shares reserved for issuance under stockholder approved equity plans, and 412,842 shares of Common Stock reserved for issuance pursuant to the Dividend Reinvestment and Stock Purchase Plan that is available to stockholders.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;">In addition, the Corporation currently intends to register and reserve for issuance and additional 2.5 million shares pursuant to the Dividend Reinvestment and Stock Purchase Plan.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The </font><font style="display: inline;">increase in the number of authorized shares to 80 million would make shares</font><font style="display: inline;"> available for issuance from time to time at the discretion of the Board, without further stockholder action except as may be required for a particular transaction by law, or other agreements and restrictions.&nbsp;&nbsp;The shares would be issuable for any proper corporate purpose, including stock splits and dividends, capital-raising transactions, including the ongoing dividend reinvestment and stock purchase plan</font><font style="display: inline;"> and </font><font style="display: inline;">the</font><font style="display: inline;"> additional shares that </font><font style="display: inline;">will</font><font style="display: inline;"> be registered pursuant thereto</font><font style="display: inline;">, future acquisitions and for equity compensation grants to employees and directors under the Corporation&#x2019;s equity compensation plans.&nbsp;&nbsp;In this regard, in 2016 the Corporation effected a 3-for-2 stock split in the form of a stock dividend.&nbsp;&nbsp;Without an increase in authorized shares of Common Stock, it is possible that the Corporation could not effectuate a similar stock split in future years.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board believes that these additional authorized shares will provide the Corporation with needed flexibility to issue shares in the future without the potential expense and delay incident to obtaining stockholder approval for a particular issuance.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;">Other than the continuation of our Dividend Reinvestment and Stock Purchase Plan, w</font><font style="display: inline;">e do not have specific plans or intentions with respect to capital raising initiatives or acquisition transactions.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">If additional shares of Common Stock are issued by the Corporation, it may potentially have an anti-takeover effect by making it more difficult to obtain shareholder approval of various actions, such as a merger or removal of management.&nbsp;&nbsp;The increase in authorized shares of Common Stock has not been proposed in connection with any anti-takeover related purpose and the Board and management have no knowledge of any current efforts by anyone to obtain control of the Corporation or to effect large accumulations of the Corporation&#x2019;s Common Stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, the issuance of additional shares of Common Stock may, among other things, have a dilutive effect on earnings per share and on the equity and voting power of existing stockholders.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The affirmative vote of the holders of at least seventy percent (70%) of the outstanding shares of Common Stock of the Corporation entitled to vote is necessary to approve the proposed amendment.&nbsp;&nbsp;Abstentions and shares not voted by brokers and other entities holding shares on behalf of the beneficial owners will have the same effect as a vote against the Proposal.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">The Board of Directors recommends a vote FOR approval of the amendment to the Certificate of Incorporation to increase the number of authorized shares of Common Stock</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">COMPENSA</font><a name="CompensationCommitteeReport"></a><font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">TION COMMITTEE REPORT</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">We have reviewed and discussed with management the Compensation Discussion and Analysis included herein and provided pursuant to Item 402(b) of Regulation S-K.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Based on this review and discussion, we recommended to the Board that the Compensation Discussion and Analysis be included in this proxy statement.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The Compensation Committee:</font>
		</p>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 20.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">

			</p>
		</td><td style="width:16pt;"><p style="width:16pt;width:16pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">

</div>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;">The preceding report shall not be deemed incorporated by reference by any general statement incorporating by reference this proxy statement into any filing under the Securities Act of 1933 (&#x201C;1933 Act&#x201D;) or the 1934 Act, except to the extent the Corporation specifically incorporates this information by reference, and shall not otherwise be deemed filed under the 1933 Act or the 1934 Act.</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">COMPENSA</font><a name="CompensationDiscussionandAnalysis"></a><font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">TION DISCUSSION AND ANALYSIS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The following is a discussion of the compensation awarded to, earned by or paid to the NEOs.&nbsp;&nbsp;The discussion explains all the material elements of the Corporation&#x2019;s compensation of the NEOs.&nbsp;&nbsp;It should be read in conjunction with the other executive compensation disclosures that appear elsewhere in this proxy statement.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">Guiding Principles</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">In designing and maintaining a compensation program for the Corporation&#x2019;s NEOs, other executive officers and employees, the Compensation Committee adheres to the following guiding principles:</font>
		</p>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (1)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">The compensation program should be principles-based, employ best practices in executive compensation and consider all relevant regulatory guidance regarding sound incentive compensation policies.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (2)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">The compensation program should be designed and supervised by the Compensation Committee with, as needed, the assistance of independent compensation consultants, legal counsel and other advisors who have significant experience in risk management, compensation practices and legal matters in the financial services industry.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (3)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">The Compensation Committee should consist entirely of independent directors and operate under a charter adopted by the Board that clearly defines its duties and responsibilities.&nbsp;&nbsp;Significant approvals by the Compensation Committee regarding the provisions of the executive compensation program and awards thereunder should be ratified by the full Board.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (4)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">A significant portion of executive compensation awarded under the program should be directly tied to corporate performance and thereby closely aligned with the interests of stockholders.&nbsp;&nbsp;The corporate performance levels necessary to earn threshold, target and maximum cash incentive and equity awards should be determined by the Compensation Committee and should not encourage inappropriate risks that could lead to material financial loss to the Bank.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (5)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">The compensation program should enable the Corporation to attract and retain highly skilled professionals in each necessary discipline (i.e., executive, financial, lending, operations, risk management).</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (6)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">Compensation paid should be appropriately balanced between short and long-term components.&nbsp;&nbsp;The short-term components should primarily consist of base salary and cash incentive compensation and the long-term components should be equity awards that vest over time as well as retirement benefits.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (7)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">The competitiveness of total direct compensation, which consists of base salary, cash incentive and equity awards, should be tested regularly by a comparison to: (1) a group of peer banks selected by the Compensation Committee that are similar in size and scope to the Corporation; and (2) amounts published in compensation surveys for the banking industry conducted by nationally recognized independent compensation consulting firms.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (8)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">The compensation program should achieve internal equity among the Corporation&#x2019;s executive officers.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (9)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">Retirement benefits should be market competitive and evaluated based on the percentage of the executive&#x2019;s income replaced in retirement.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (10)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">Payments upon a change in control or termination should be market competitive, reasonable in amount and designed to ensure that the executive officers of the Bank are not significantly harmed nor unduly enriched and are therefore objective with respect to the consummation of a transaction, such as a sale or merger of the Bank, that may be in the best interests of the Corporation&#x2019;s stockholders. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (11)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">The Compensation Committee should identify those employees, whether they are executive officers or otherwise, who could potentially expose the Corporation to material amounts of risk.&nbsp;&nbsp;The compensation of such employees should be designed to discourage imprudent risk taking and contain maximum incentive amounts that do not represent windfalls.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (12)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">Clawbacks should be utilized within the compensation program in accordance with our clawback policy and applicable law.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (13)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">Retention of vested or exercised equity awards should be required until stock ownership guidelines are met.&nbsp; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (14)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">Employees, whether they are executive officers or otherwise, should be prohibited from hedging the value of equity compensation that vests over time.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (15)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">Performance goals should be established by the Compensation Committee and ratified by the full Board.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 22.00pt;">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;"> (16)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:14pt;"><p style="width:14pt;width:14pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">Achievement of performance goals should be certified by the Compensation Committee </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">prior to the payment of awards.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 8pt;line-height:107.92%;text-align:left;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;"></font><font style="display: inline;">14</font><font style="display: inline;"></font>

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 8pt">

			<a href="#TableofContents"><font style="display: inline;font-size:8pt;">Table of Contents</font></a>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 8pt;line-height:107.92%;text-align:left;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;"></font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">Objectives of the Executive Compensation Program</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The Corporation&#x2019;s executive compensation program is designed to enable the Corporation to attract and retain talented executive officers necessary to safely and successfully operate and grow the Bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;The executive compensation program promotes sound risk management and long-term value creation for our stockholders. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">What the Executive Compensation Program is Designed to Reward</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Certain elements of the executive compensation program are intended to reward current performance.&nbsp;&nbsp;By offering long-term equity compensation, the executive compensation program is also designed to reward executive officers who help maximize long-term financial performance and earnings growth of the Corporation.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">Elements of Executive Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The executive compensation program consists of four basic components: (1) base salary; (2) annual cash incentive compensation; (3) equity awards; and (4) other noncash compensation, consisting primarily of retirement benefits and reasonable perquisites. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">Why We Choose To Pay Each Element of Executive Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:18pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;">Base Salary.</font><font style="display: inline;"> &nbsp;The Compensation Committee believes that base salary for a named executive officer should compensate the officer for the skills and effort required to perform the officer&#x2019;s day-to-day responsibilities, taking into account the size and complexity of the Company.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:18pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;">Annual Cash Incentive Compensation.</font><font style="display: inline;"> &nbsp;The Compensation Committee has included annual cash incentive compensation in the executive compensation program as a means to incent executive officers to optimize corporate performance through, among other things, the achievement of annual corporate goals set forth in the Corporation&#x2019;s strategic plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our Compensation Committee recommended, the Board adopted and the stockholders approved the 2016 Cash Incentive Plan, which provides the opportunity for a cash incentive payment based upon the achievement of corporate and individual goals. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:18pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;">Equity Awards</font><font style="display: inline;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Compensation Committee uses equity awards granted under the Corporation&#x2019;s equity incentive plan as a means to incent executive officers to optimize corporate performance over an extended time-period.&nbsp;&nbsp;Equity awards, together with retirement benefits, are the longer-term components of executive compensation.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:18pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;">Other Noncash Compensation.</font><font style="display: inline;"> &nbsp;Other noncash compensation consists of: (1) retirement benefits paid under the Bank&#x2019;s defined benefit pension plan (&#x201C;Pension Plan&#x201D;), 401(k) Plan and Supplemental Executive Retirement Plan (&#x201C;SERP&#x201D;); and (2) noncash fringe benefits not available to the general employee population of the Bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;Noncash fringe benefits, other than those available to the general employee population at the Bank, include the personal use of business automobiles and a country club membership for the CEO.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Retirement benefits provided by the Corporation&#x2019;s Pension and 401(k) Plans are intended to encourage the NEOs to maintain their employment with the Corporation and maximize long-term corporate performance.&nbsp;&nbsp;The SERP, of which the CEO is the only participant, provides the additional pension and 401(k) benefits that the CEO would receive in the absence of Internal Revenue Code provisions which limit the amount of compensation that can be considered in determining retirement benefits to be paid under the Bank&#x2019;s tax-qualified retirement plans.&nbsp;&nbsp;The SERP is explained in the &#x201C;PENSION BENEFITS&#x201D; section of this proxy statement.&nbsp;&nbsp;A country club membership is provided to the CEO to aid him in developing and retaining business.&nbsp;&nbsp;Business automobiles are provided to all of the Bank&#x2019;s executive officers as a competitive perquisite and as an alternative to reimbursing such officers for mileage driven on account of business conducted on behalf of the Corporation.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;">How We Determine The Amount To Pay For Each Element of Executive Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The total compensation paid by the Corporation to each of the NEOs is based on a variety of factors including: (1) the Company&#x2019;s recent and expected future overall financial performance; (2) current economic conditions and the effect thereof on the Company&#x2019;s performance and that of its peers; (3) the executive officer&#x2019;s experience and tenure in his or her current position, years of service to the Bank, scope of responsibilities, leadership ability, compensation relative to the Company&#x2019;s other executive officers, recent and expected future performance, and contributions to corporate performance; (4) a comparison of total compensation and each element of compensation paid to the executive to compensation amounts paid by peer banks to executives with similar roles and compensation amounts set forth in published industry surveys for executives with similar roles; and (5) the most recent stockholder advisory vote on executive compensation.&nbsp;&nbsp;As previously discussed, comparative compensation studies are performed and updated on a periodic basis by an independent compensation consulting firm engaged by and working under the direction of the Compensation Committee.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Base salary for the CEO is reviewed by the Compensation Committee on an annual basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Compensation Committee also performs an annual review of the base salary recommendations made by the CEO for the Company&#x2019;s other NEOs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each executive officer does not necessarily receive an increase in base salary each year.&nbsp;&nbsp;In reviewing each named executive officer&#x2019;s base salary, the Compensation Committee considers the amounts paid by peer banks, the amounts set forth in compensation surveys performed by nationally recognized independent compensation consulting firms and the Corporation&#x2019;s overall budget for base salary increases.&nbsp;&nbsp;Regular annual salary increases for 2017 for the NEOs ranged from 3.3% to 14.3% and averaged 6.9%.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;"></font><font style="display: inline;">15</font><font style="display: inline;"></font>

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 8pt">

			<a href="#TableofContents"><font style="display: inline;font-size:8pt;">Table of Contents</font></a>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;">For the Corporation&#x2019;s CEO and the Senior Executive Vice President,</font><font style="display: inline;"> annual</font><font style="display: inline;"> cash incentive compensat</font><font style="display: inline;">ion has been</font><font style="display: inline;"> based entirely on corporate performance measured by net income, ROA and bank safety.&nbsp;&nbsp;Cash incentive compensation for the other NEOs, except Mr. Daley, </font><font style="display: inline;">ha</font><font style="display: inline;">s &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">been </font><font style="display: inline;">based on a combination of corporate and personal performance, with corporate performance weighted 80% and personal performance weighted 20%.&nbsp;&nbsp;For Mr. Dale</font><font style="display: inline;">y, cash incentive compensation ha</font><font style="display: inline;">s</font><font style="display: inline;"> also</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">been </font><font style="display: inline;">based on a combination of corporate and personal performance, with corporate performance weighted 50% and personal performance weighted 50%.&nbsp;&nbsp;Personal performance is measured by the achievement of goals, monetary and nonmonetary, assigned to the NEO.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The following table sets forth the range of annual cash incentive compensation for 2017 under the 2016 Cash Incentive Plan assuming that the Corporation achieved threshold, target and maximum levels of performance and, where applicable, the NEO achieved threshold, target and maximum levels of performance with respect to personal goals.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each NEO&#x2019;s cash incentive target for 2017 was a percentage of base salary as determined by the Compensation Committee.&nbsp;&nbsp;Achievement of corporate and where applicable personal performance levels greater than the threshold level but less than the maximum level results in a cash incentive payment that is proportionately greater than the threshold level of incentive but less than the maximum level of incentive. </font>
		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;text-indent:0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Equity incentive compensation for the NEOs has primarily consisted of performance-based RSUs, but has also occasionally included smaller amounts of time-based RSUs.&nbsp;&nbsp;The receipt of performance-based RSUs </font><font style="display: inline;">ha</font><font style="display: inline;">s &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">been </font><font style="display: inline;">based entirely on corporate performance measured by the same metrics used for cash incentive compensation and the receipt of time-based RSUs </font><font style="display: inline;">ha</font><font style="display: inline;">s &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">been </font><font style="display: inline;">based on the discretion of the Compensation Committee after considering, among other things, the strength and consistency of the Corporation&#x2019;s performance over an extended period of time. Performance-based RSUs </font><font style="display: inline;">granted before January 2018 vest and </font><font style="display: inline;">convert into shares of Common Stock based on the satisfaction of net income and ROA performance metrics for the final year of the three calendar year performance period beginning with the year in which the RSUs were awarded.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;">Two</font><font style="display: inline;">-</font><font style="display: inline;">thirds </font><font style="display: inline;">(</font><font style="display: inline;">2/3</font><font style="display: inline;">) of the RSUs granted in January 201</font><font style="display: inline;">8 are performance-based and one-</font><font style="display: inline;">third (1/3) are time-based. One</font><font style="display: inline;">-</font><font style="display: inline;">third (1/3) vests and converts into shares of Common Stock based on the satisfaction of net income and ROA performance metrics for 2018, one</font><font style="display: inline;">-</font><font style="display: inline;">third (1/3) vests and converts based on the satisfaction of net income and ROA performance metr</font><font style="display: inline;">ics for 2019 and the final one-</font><font style="display: inline;">third (1/3) vests and converts three years from the date of grant. Multi</font><font style="display: inline;">-year performance period</font><font style="display: inline;">s</font><font style="display: inline;"> for the performance-based RSUs encourages long-term strategic focus.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">For outstanding performance-based RSUs granted before January 2017, the threshold level of performance will result in a conversion ratio of one RSU for one-half (&#xBD;) share of Common Stock and performance at or above the target level will result in a conversion ratio of one RSU for one share of Common Stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;Performance greater than the threshold level but less than the target level will result in a conversion ratio proportionately greater than one RSU for one-half (&#xBD;) share of Common Stock but less than one RSU for one share of Common Stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;If performance falls below the threshold level, the RSUs will expire and not be convertible into shares of the Corporation&#x2019;s Common Stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;Unlike previous RSU grants, performance-based RSUs granted in January 2017 and 2018 have upside conversion potential in that a maximum level of performance will result in a conversion ratio of one RSU for one-and-one-quarter (1&#xBC;) and one-and-one-half (1&#xBD;) shares of Common Stock, respectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;Performance greater than the threshold level but less than the maximum level will result in a conversion ratio proportionately greater than one RSU for one-half (&#xBD;) share of Common Stock but less than one RSU for one-and-one-quarter (1&#xBC;) or one-and-one-half (1&#xBD;) shares of Common Stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;The maximum level of performance for RSUs granted before January 2018 has been 125% of the target level, whereas the threshold level of performance has been 75% of the target level.&nbsp;&nbsp;For the RSUs granted in January 2018, the maximum level of performance is 115% of the target level, whereas the threshold level of performance is 80% of the target level.&nbsp;&nbsp;For the RSUs granted before January 2018, exceeding the target level of performance by 25% results in vesting 25% more than the target level of shares, while falling 25% short of the target level of performance results in vesting 50% less than the target level of shares.&nbsp;&nbsp;For the RSUs granted in January 2018, exceeding the target level of performance by 15% results in vesting 50% more than the target level of shares, while falling 20% short of the target level of performance results in vesting 50% less than the target level of shares.&nbsp;&nbsp;Falling short by more than 25% for the prior RSU grants and 20% for the January 2018 grant results in expiration of the RSUs without any vesting of the target level of shares.&nbsp;&nbsp;The punitive impact of falling short of the target level of performance and the upside potential for exceeding the target level of performance is designed to encourage senior management to outperform.&nbsp;&nbsp;In setting threshold, target and maximum levels of performance and </font><font style="display: inline;">related</font><font style="display: inline;"> payouts, the Compensation Committee has considered, among other things, performance and payout levels for the Corporation&#x2019;s peer banks.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Over the last three years, cash incentive compensation for the NEOs as a group</font><font style="display: inline;"> has averaged approximately one-</font><font style="display: inline;">third (1/3) of total incentive compensation, while equity incentive compensation has averaged approximately two</font><font style="display: inline;">-</font><font style="display: inline;">thirds of total incentive compensation.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;"></font><font style="display: inline;">16</font><font style="display: inline;"></font>

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 8pt">

			<a href="#TableofContents"><font style="display: inline;font-size:8pt;">Table of Contents</font></a>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;">By their terms, all outstanding performance-based RSUs held by NEOs immediately vest in the event of an involuntary termination following a change in control, total and permanent disability, as defined, or death and for those performance-based RSUs granted in January 2018, immediately vest in the event of retirement.&nbsp;&nbsp;For performance-based RSUs granted before January 2018 to NEOs, other than the CFO, in the event of retirement, and in order to qualify as tax-deductible performance-based compensation under the pre-2018 provisions of Section 162(m) of the Internal Revenue Code, vesting can only occur upon completion of the related performance period and attainment of the relevant performance criteria.&nbsp;&nbsp;The performance-based RSUs granted to the CFO before January 2018 immediately vest in the event of retirement because the CFO is exempt from the pre-2018 provisions of Section 162(m).&nbsp;&nbsp;All outstanding time-based RSUs granted to NEOs immediately vest in the event of an involuntary termination following a change in control, total and permanent disability, as defined, or death, and, unlike</font><font style="display: inline;"> many of</font><font style="display: inline;"> the performance-based RSUs, also immediately vest in the event of retirement.&nbsp;&nbsp;For a further discussion of the tax-deductibility of executive compensation, see Tax Deductibility of Executive Compensation section of this proxy statement. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The value of a RSU realized at vesting can be more or less than its grant date fair value if the Common Stock price at the date of vesting is more or less than its fair market value on the date of grant</font><font style="display: inline;"> or</font><font style="display: inline;"> the aggregate conversion ratio described above is </font><font style="display: inline;">more or </font><font style="display: inline;">less than one RSU f</font><font style="display: inline;">or one share of Common Stock.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The following table sets forth the range for the grant date fair value of performance-based equity incentive compensation for 2017 performance assuming that the Corporation achieved threshold, target and maximum levels of performance.&nbsp;&nbsp;Achievement of corporate performance levels greater than the threshold level but less than the maximum level</font><font style="display: inline;"> has</font><font style="display: inline;"> result</font><font style="display: inline;">ed</font><font style="display: inline;"> in a grant of equity awards that is proportionately greater than the threshold grant of equity awards but less than the maximum grant of equity awards.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 1pt">

				<td valign="bottom" style="width:25.00%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt solid #000000 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt solid #000000 ;background-color: #CCEEFF;height:12.75pt;padding:0pt;">

				</td>

				</td>
				<td valign="bottom" style="width:25.00%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt solid #000000 ;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000 ;border-right:1pt solid #000000 ;background-color: #CCEEFF;height:12.75pt;padding:0pt;">

				</td>
				<td valign="bottom" style="width:25.00%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt solid #000000 ;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000 ;border-right:1pt solid #000000 ;background-color: #CCEEFF;height:12.75pt;padding:0pt;">
